00:41:15,319 --> 00:41:18,039
I run forward through the ribs,

1102
00:41:18,039 --> 00:41:20,079
but like singing in the rain style.

1103
00:41:20,079 --> 00:41:23,759
So I'm kind of like swinging off of each of the ones.

1104
00:41:23,759 --> 00:41:25,880
I'm just happy to be back on the ground.

1105
00:41:27,000 --> 00:41:28,960
Twirling around them.

1106
00:41:28,960 --> 00:41:31,039
As you guys kind of get off the boat,

1107
00:41:31,039 --> 00:41:34,480
Larry says, if it's all the same to you guys,

1108
00:41:34,480 --> 00:41:37,360
I would like to keep my crewman on the ship,

1109
00:41:37,360 --> 00:41:41,360
being that if this is, in fact, a dragon's lair,

1110
00:41:41,360 --> 00:41:44,240
I don't want to leave my ship unguarded.

1111
00:41:44,240 --> 00:41:45,320
Fair enough.

1112
00:41:45,320 --> 00:41:47,599
Yep, you guys are pretty useless anyway.

1113
00:41:47,599 --> 00:41:50,160
And it did prove to be a very safe place

1114
00:41:50,160 --> 00:41:52,079
for all of your crewmen on the boat.

1115
00:41:52,079 --> 00:41:53,240
I kind of more muttered that.

1116
00:41:53,240 --> 00:41:54,039
I don't want to be rude,

1117
00:41:54,039 --> 00:41:56,039
but I do want to talk a little bit of shit

1118
00:41:56,039 --> 00:41:57,760
just to you guys about him.

1119
00:41:57,760 --> 00:42:00,120
So, like, whatever.

1120
00:42:00,120 --> 00:42:01,400
No problem there.

1121
00:42:01,400 --> 00:42:02,720
It's time for a break, obviously.

1122
00:42:02,720 --> 00:42:04,519
Well, you know, we've been traveling long enough.

1123
00:42:04,519 --> 00:42:05,840
We're all getting a bit irritated with each other.

1124
00:42:05,840 --> 00:42:07,480
We've got a little cabin fever setting in.

1125
00:42:07,480 --> 00:42:08,559
Yeah, yeah.

1126
00:42:08,559 --> 00:42:12,320
An ice chasm splits the cliff face above the ice shelf

1127
00:42:12,320 --> 00:42:14,360
rising to the top of the plateau.

1128
00:42:14,360 --> 00:42:17,280
And the chasm is about 20 feet wide near the bottom,

1129
00:42:17,280 --> 00:42:19,880
but narrows to five feet wide at the top.

1130
00:42:19,880 --> 00:42:22,480
And steps are cut into the ice,

1131
00:42:22,480 --> 00:42:26,920
making for an easy climb up to the top of the plateau.

1132
00:42:26,920 --> 00:42:30,480
As you get up to the top, it's not level.

1133
00:42:30,480 --> 00:42:33,079
The ground is uneven and fractured

1134
00:42:33,079 --> 00:42:35,039
by different narrow ice chasms.

1135
00:42:35,079 --> 00:42:38,360
You see, when you come up to the top of the plateau,

1136
00:42:38,360 --> 00:42:43,360
in a row, there are 10 corpses frozen into a wall of ice.

1137
00:42:45,480 --> 00:42:48,719
You see three Lusker warriors, a dwarf,

1138
00:42:48,719 --> 00:42:52,559
and six of the people who look the same

1139
00:42:52,559 --> 00:42:55,000
as those who you were talking to in the canoes.

1140
00:42:55,000 --> 00:42:57,119
The bodies have been preserved in the ice,

1141
00:42:57,119 --> 00:43:00,119
making it impossible to tell how long they've been there.

1142
00:43:00,119 --> 00:43:02,079
But that's what you see as you walk up there.

1143
00:43:02,079 --> 00:43:05,400
And there is a bit of a footpath

1144
00:43:05,400 --> 00:43:07,840
that continues along more towards the center

1145
00:43:07,840 --> 00:43:09,199
of this iceberg.

1146
00:43:09,199 --> 00:43:13,880
I stop in front of one of the frozen people,

1147
00:43:13,880 --> 00:43:16,119
and I look back at Plinthi and go,

1148
00:43:16,119 --> 00:43:18,039
should I like thaw one of them out

1149
00:43:18,039 --> 00:43:19,840
and see if they're still alive?

1150
00:43:19,840 --> 00:43:21,279
They can maybe tell us how they got here

1151
00:43:21,279 --> 00:43:22,400
and what's going on.

1152
00:43:24,400 --> 00:43:26,679
How's your resurrection magic?

1153
00:43:26,679 --> 00:43:27,519
It's not.

1154
00:43:27,519 --> 00:43:29,559
So I could thaw them and they could just be dead,

1155
00:43:29,559 --> 00:43:32,159
or they could be just frozen.

1156
00:43:32,159 --> 00:43:35,840
And when I thaw them out, they'll probably still be dead.

1157
00:43:35,840 --> 00:43:39,199
But they mean they could be alive.

1158
00:43:39,199 --> 00:43:41,079
I think we could probably leave.

1159
00:43:41,079 --> 00:43:42,039
Okay.

1160
00:43:42,039 --> 00:43:42,880
Maybe next time.

1161
00:43:42,880 --> 00:43:44,840
Well, if nothing else turns up,

1162
00:43:44,840 --> 00:43:48,039
let's come back and unthaw one of these bad boys.

1163
00:43:48,039 --> 00:43:49,599
I patch the ice and I'm like,

1164
00:43:49,599 --> 00:43:51,039
maybe next time you guys,

1165
00:43:51,039 --> 00:43:53,920
I'll get my necromancy under check.

1166
00:43:53,920 --> 00:43:54,759
Love it.

1167
00:43:54,759 --> 00:43:57,400
There is an obvious path,

1168
00:43:57,400 --> 00:43:59,280
which looks to be that of,

1169
00:43:59,280 --> 00:44:00,800
which has been made by the hunters

1170
00:44:00,800 --> 00:44:03,240
who you saw in the canoe

1171
00:44:03,240 --> 00:44:05,119
leading towards the center of the iceberg there.

1172
00:44:05,119 --> 00:44:05,960
Off we go.

1173
00:44:05,960 --> 00:44:07,960
Yeah, I'm already on the path.

1174
00:44:09,960 --> 00:44:13,360
As you travel along it,

1175
00:44:13,360 --> 00:44:15,280
it doesn't take a long time

1176
00:44:15,280 --> 00:44:18,960
before you see smoke rising

1177
00:44:18,960 --> 00:44:21,240
over some of the snow drifts

1178
00:44:21,240 --> 00:44:23,160
and some of the different chasms and stuff

1179
00:44:23,160 --> 00:44:26,039
that you're walking through and around.

1180
00:44:26,079 --> 00:44:29,920
You see smoke rising from the center of the iceberg

1181
00:44:29,920 --> 00:44:34,400
in very chimney-esque type streams.

1182
00:44:34,400 --> 00:44:36,239
Guys, I think we should go there immediately.

1183
00:44:36,239 --> 00:44:37,079
Agreed.

1184
00:44:37,079 --> 00:44:37,920
What else are we doing?

1185
00:44:37,920 --> 00:44:38,759
We hurry faster thinking

1186
00:44:38,759 --> 00:44:41,159
that there might be a warm place.

1187
00:44:41,159 --> 00:44:43,440
As you approach,

1188
00:44:43,440 --> 00:44:46,400
there's a large chasm and ice ledge.

1189
00:44:46,400 --> 00:44:51,400
You are noticed by a pack of sled dogs

1190
00:44:51,679 --> 00:44:53,519
that is a little bit further ahead there,

1191
00:44:53,519 --> 00:44:55,639
and they begin barking and growling

1192
00:44:56,599 --> 00:44:59,199
as you enter into this open area

1193
00:44:59,199 --> 00:45:01,719
