like anything negative about dragons,

1367
00:51:21,880 --> 00:51:24,280
we want to just like really focus

1368
00:51:24,280 --> 00:51:28,720
on how we're trying to find that woman and that ship.

1369
00:51:28,720 --> 00:51:29,920
Like that's what we're,

1370
00:51:29,920 --> 00:51:32,600
have they seen anything like that?

1371
00:51:32,600 --> 00:51:35,240
You describe Makoth the Crimson

1372
00:51:35,240 --> 00:51:39,640
and he kind of takes a pause and says,

1373
00:51:39,640 --> 00:51:43,720
we've heard stories of her and her ship,

1374
00:51:43,720 --> 00:51:46,160
but they were destroyed years ago

1375
00:51:46,160 --> 00:51:48,000
by a dragon named-

1376
00:51:48,000 --> 00:51:49,080
Aruthator.

1377
00:51:49,080 --> 00:51:51,680
Well, he uses the phrase old white death.

1378
00:51:51,680 --> 00:51:53,400
Yeah, sounds like the same guy.

1379
00:51:53,400 --> 00:51:56,480
But in fact, the dragon itself

1380
00:51:56,480 --> 00:51:59,240
was killed a year ago by frost giants.

1381
00:51:59,240 --> 00:52:00,600
Oh, twist.

1382
00:52:00,600 --> 00:52:01,760
Twist indeed.

1383
00:52:02,760 --> 00:52:06,360
He starts describing how they are living here

1384
00:52:06,360 --> 00:52:10,000
and that you guys need to leave right away

1385
00:52:10,000 --> 00:52:14,440
as there are many different sea monsters in the area.

1386
00:52:14,440 --> 00:52:19,160
And he tells you that he is surprised

1387
00:52:19,160 --> 00:52:21,280
that you walked past the ice shelf

1388
00:52:21,280 --> 00:52:24,720
as those are all the bones of the monsters

1389
00:52:24,720 --> 00:52:28,120
that they have killed in trying to keep people away

1390
00:52:28,120 --> 00:52:29,400
from where they are staying.

1391
00:52:29,440 --> 00:52:32,240
They're saying they killed the whales

1392
00:52:32,240 --> 00:52:35,360
and the giant seals, like the rib tunnel.

1393
00:52:35,360 --> 00:52:38,240
He did not refer to them as whales or seals.

1394
00:52:38,240 --> 00:52:41,599
He referred to them as bones of sea monsters.

1395
00:52:41,599 --> 00:52:43,880
I do not think this group is very educated.

1396
00:52:43,880 --> 00:52:45,000
But also they're lying

1397
00:52:45,000 --> 00:52:46,880
because there's teeth marks on them,

1398
00:52:46,880 --> 00:52:48,480
like giant teeth marks.

1399
00:52:48,480 --> 00:52:49,840
So how'd they kill them?

1400
00:52:49,840 --> 00:52:51,599
They're pulling our legs here.

1401
00:52:51,599 --> 00:52:53,559
Call a note on it, Eulara.

1402
00:52:53,559 --> 00:52:55,160
Well, so we can ask like,

1403
00:52:55,160 --> 00:52:57,639
oh, it looked like there was teeth marks

1404
00:52:57,639 --> 00:53:00,799
on those giant bones though, huh?

1405
00:53:02,319 --> 00:53:04,719
Without being accusatory, but you know.

1406
00:53:04,719 --> 00:53:09,279
He takes a second and looks like he's searching

1407
00:53:09,279 --> 00:53:11,920
for the right thing to say,

1408
00:53:11,920 --> 00:53:14,839
but then says, you must just leave

1409
00:53:14,839 --> 00:53:18,920
for the safety of our tribe and for your safety.

1410
00:53:18,920 --> 00:53:21,359
There is nothing for you here.

1411
00:53:21,359 --> 00:53:22,960
Can I ask him,

1412
00:53:22,960 --> 00:53:27,559
before the ice giant defeated Arithator,

1413
00:53:28,480 --> 00:53:29,320
who's now dead,

1414
00:53:30,799 --> 00:53:33,759
were they ruled over by this dragon?

1415
00:53:33,759 --> 00:53:36,599
He does not say, but a look in his eye

1416
00:53:36,599 --> 00:53:40,119
gives you the feeling that there is something

1417
00:53:40,119 --> 00:53:41,679
that he is very concerned about.

1418
00:53:41,679 --> 00:53:44,840
Do the ice giants rule this land?

1419
00:53:44,840 --> 00:53:46,679
He says, no.

1420
00:53:46,679 --> 00:53:48,920
Is Arithator the dragon actually dead?

1421
00:53:48,920 --> 00:53:52,239
He avoids the question and says,

1422
00:53:52,239 --> 00:53:53,199
I've got my answer.

1423
00:53:53,199 --> 00:53:55,320
If you do not leave,

1424
00:53:55,480 --> 00:53:58,880
Arithator is gonna be pissed and destroy your village.

1425
00:53:58,880 --> 00:54:01,039
If you do not leave,

1426
00:54:01,039 --> 00:54:04,480
we will force your strongest warrior

1427
00:54:04,480 --> 00:54:06,519
to battle our strongest warrior.

1428
00:54:06,519 --> 00:54:08,760
Would this get us the answers to the questions

1429
00:54:08,760 --> 00:54:09,600
that we've been asking?

1430
00:54:09,600 --> 00:54:12,480
Because we're not above a fight or anything.

1431
00:54:12,480 --> 00:54:15,920
I'd prefer to work together to solve this problem

1432
00:54:15,920 --> 00:54:18,880
as opposed to kill your strongest warrior.

1433
00:54:18,880 --> 00:54:21,360
That just sounds like a backwards step to it.

1434
00:54:21,360 --> 00:54:24,519
Do they need help fighting the frost giants?

1435
00:54:24,559 --> 00:54:25,639
Because we're all over that.

1436
00:54:25,639 --> 00:54:27,599
Yeah, we are very helpful.

1437
00:54:27,599 --> 00:54:28,880
We don't want to fight them.

1438
00:54:28,880 --> 00:54:33,360
He says, if you feel you can help us,

1439
00:54:33,360 --> 00:54:36,759
the only way I know that you can prove this

1440
00:54:36,759 --> 00:54:38,880
is to battle our strongest warrior.

1441
00:54:38,880 --> 00:54:39,840
Do we have to kill him?

1442
00:54:39,840 --> 00:54:40,679
I don't really want to kill him.

1443
00:54:40,679 --> 00:54:41,519
Me neither.

1444
00:54:41,519 --> 00:54:43,679
I really don't want to kill your strongest warrior.

1445
00:54:43,679 --> 00:54:44,639
I mean, we can like-

1446
00:54:44,639 --> 00:54:46,280
Can we just fight till-

1447
00:54:46,280 --> 00:54:47,119
Like main?

1448
00:54:47,119 --> 00:54:47,940
Or even-

1449
00:54:47,940 --> 00:54:49,400
Fight until he gets too tired?

1450
00:54:49,400 --> 00:54:53,199
Or fight until we could have struck a killing blow,

1451
00:54:53,200 --> 00:54:55,600
but not actually, you know what I mean?

1452
00:54:55,600 --> 00:54:57,680
Like how they would fight, like a training fight.

1453
00:54:57,680 --> 00:54:59,640
The battle must be to the death.

1454
00:54:59,640 --> 00:55:00,480
All right, fine.

1455
00:55:00,480 --> 00:55:01,300
Let's do this.

1456
00:55:01,300 --> 00:55:03,400
Why do you want us to kill your strongest warrior?

1457
00:55:03,400 --> 00:55:04,720
So bad.

1458
00:55:04,720 --> 00:55:05,560
You know what?

1459
00:55:05,560 --> 00:55:06,760
Maybe they don't trust the strongest warrior.

1460
00:55:06,760 --> 00:55:08,160
Maybe he's in cahoots with them.

1461
00:55:08,160 --> 00:55:10,040
Maybe he's just trying to get us to do his dirty work.

1462
00:55:10,040 --> 00:55:10,920
Who knows?

1463
00:55:10,920 --> 00:55:12,640
Which one of us is going to murder

1464
00:55:12,640 --> 00:55:14,240
perhaps a very innocent person?

1465
00:55:14,240 --> 00:55:18,000
He says one of the stipulations of this battle

1466
00:55:18,000 --> 00:55:19,760
is that it must be one-on-one.

1467
00:55:19,760 --> 00:55:21,840
No magic is allowed.

1468
00:55:22,640 --> 00:55:24,200
No.

1469
00:55:24,200 --> 00:55:27,200
And the fight continues until one contestant

1470
00:55:27,200 --> 00:55:29,079
is unconscious and dying.

1471
00:55:29,079 --> 00:55:30,920
Ooh, so not necessarily dead-dead.

1472
00:55:30,920 --> 00:55:32,760
All right, I volunteer as tribute.

1473
00:55:32,760 --> 00:55:34,600
Yes, I was going to say.

1474
00:55:34,600 --> 00:55:35,760
Also, what do these people look like?

1475
00:55:35,760 --> 00:55:36,600
Are they human?

1476
00:55:36,600 --> 00:55:37,480
Humanoid?

1477
00:55:37,480 --> 00:55:38,320
Yeah.

1478
00:55:38,320 --> 00:55:39,160
Humanesque.

1479
00:55:39,160 --> 00:55:40,640
Yeah, very human, humanesque.

1480
00:55:40,640 --> 00:55:41,480
Human-like.

1481
00:55:41,480 --> 00:55:42,320
Yeah, Flint.

1482
00:55:42,320 --> 00:55:45,000
Also, I don't want you to turn your flaming sword on

1483
00:55:45,000 --> 00:55:46,400
and be disqualified, so.

1484
00:55:46,400 --> 00:55:48,800
Oh, yeah, I guess that's magic.

1485
00:55:48,800 --> 00:55:49,960
That's a really good point.

1486
00:55:49,960 --> 00:55:51,720
Yeah, Flint is like the least magic we have

1487
00:55:51,720 --> 00:55:53,040
with the most strength.

1488
00:55:53,040 --> 00:55:54,440
Knock him down, Flint.

1489
00:55:54,440 --> 00:55:55,840
Let's do this.

1490
00:55:55,840 --> 00:55:57,480
You've accepted the battle.

1491
00:55:57,480 --> 00:55:59,400
So you are brought out.

1492
00:55:59,400 --> 00:56:00,880
You're allowed one weapon.

1493
00:56:00,880 --> 00:56:02,960
I will take my two-handed great axe,

1494
00:56:02,960 --> 00:56:03,800
thank you very much.

1495
00:56:03,800 --> 00:56:05,320
And your armor, of course.

1496
00:56:05,320 --> 00:56:07,040
But you guys are brought out

1497
00:56:07,040 --> 00:56:08,840
to the center of the village.

1498
00:56:08,840 --> 00:56:10,440
All of the people from the village

1499
00:56:10,440 --> 00:56:12,120
are encircling the area.

1500
00:56:12,120 --> 00:56:16,000
And you come out and you are greeted by

1501
00:56:16,000 --> 00:56:20,280
a very large man

1502
00:56:20,280 --> 00:56:23,960
dressed in full gladiator-type armor.

1503
00:56:23,960 --> 00:56:27,720
And he is probably at least double your size,

1504
00:56:27,720 --> 00:56:30,080
